Explanation:

The solution uses a while loop to repeatedly compare the lengths of the two strings and update the result string accordingly. After each iteration, it updates the temporary strings temp1 and temp2 to ensure both strings are updated with the smaller string's characters. The algorithm maintains a constant space complexity of O(1) since it only uses a single string for the result. The time complexity is O(n), where n is the length of the shorter string, as the algorithm iterates until both strings are empty.

